From 1581b5e0f0000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tim 'mithro' Ansell <me@mith.ro>
Date: Sat, 12 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0930
Subject: [PATCH] Fix SD card routing: use EMMC2 instead of EMMC1 for mmcblk0

The GPIO SD bus multiplexer linked "sdbus-sdhci" to the base SoC's
SDHCI (EMMC1 at 0x300000), causing the SD card to appear as mmcblk1.
On real RPi 4B, the SD card uses EMMC2 (at 0x340000), which the DTB
aliases as mmc0 -> mmcblk0.  Redirect the link to EMMC2 so RPi OS
can find root=/dev/mmcblk0p2.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 hw/arm/bcm2838_peripherals.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/hw/arm/bcm2838_peripherals.c b/hw/arm/bcm2838_peripherals.c
index 47b0f588f..1581b5e0f 100644
--- a/hw/arm/bcm2838_peripherals.c
+++ b/hw/arm/bcm2838_peripherals.c
@@ -60,7 +60,7 @@ static void bcm2838_peripherals_init(Object *obj)
     object_initialize_child(obj, "gpio", &s->gpio, TYPE_BCM2838_GPIO);
 
     object_property_add_const_link(OBJECT(&s->gpio), "sdbus-sdhci",
-                                   OBJECT(&s_base->sdhci.sdbus));
+                                   OBJECT(&s->emmc2.sdbus));
     object_property_add_const_link(OBJECT(&s->gpio), "sdbus-sdhost",
                                    OBJECT(&s_base->sdhost.sdbus));
 
